quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  31,22,"But he who Surrenders his purpose unto Allah (i.e. becomes a Muslim), and does good, he has grasped the firm handle; with Allah rests the issue of all affairs"
  31,23,"But he who disbelieves, let not his disbelief grieve you; to Us is their return, and We will inform them of what they did; for, verily, Allah is aware of what is in the heart of men"
  31,24,We will let them enjoy themselves a little; then We will force them to the unrelenting doom
  31,25,"And if you should ask them who created the heavens and the earth, they will surely say, \"Allah.\" Say, \"Praise be to Allah!\" but most of them know not"
  31,26,"Unto Allah belongs all that is in the heavens and that is in the earth; verily, Allah, He is the Absolute, the Owner of praise"
  31,27,"And were the trees that are in the earth pens, and the sea ink with seven more seas to swell it, the Words of Allah would not be exhausted; verily, Allah is Mighty, Wise"
  31,28,"Your creation and your rising again are but as that of a single soul; verily, Allah is Hearer, Seer"
  31,29,"Have you not seen that Allah joins the night to the day, and joins the day to the night, and has subjected the sun and the moon, each running unto an appointed time? And that Allah is well informed of what you do"
  31,30,"That is because Allah, He is Truth (or the only Reality), and because what you call on beside Him is the False, and because Allah, He is the Sublime, the Great"
  31,31,"Do you not see that the ship rides on in the sea by the favour of Allah, that He may show you of His wonders? Verily, in that are signs to every grateful heart"
  31,32,"And when a wave like a shadow covers them, they call on Allah, being sincere in their religion; and when He saves them to the shore, then amongst them are some who halt between two opinions. But none denies Our signs save every perfidious disbeliever"
  31,33,"O mankind! Fear (keep your duty to) your Lord and dread the Day when the parent shall not be able to avail the child in aught, nor shall the child avail aught for its parent. Lo! the promise of Allah is true! Say, \"Let not the life of this world begu"
  31,34,"Verily, Allah, with Him is the knowledge of the Hour; He sends down the rain; and He knows that which is in the wombs. No soul knows what it is that it shall earn to-morrow; and no soul knows in what land it will die. Verily, Allah is Knower, Aware"
  32,1,Alif Lam Mim
  32,2,"The revelation of the Book, wherein there is no doubt, is from the Lord of the Worlds"
  32,3,"Or do they say, \"He (Muhammad) has invented it? Nay! It is the truth from your Lord that you may warn a people to whom no Warner has come before you, that they may follow the right direction"
  32,4,"Allah is He Who created the heavens and the earth and what is between them in six Days (periods), and He mounted the Throne (of authority); you have not besides Him any guardian or any intercessor, will you not then remember"
  32,5,He directs the ordinance (regulates all affairs) from the heaven to the earth; then shall it ascend to Him in a Day the measure of which is a thousand years of what you count
  32,6,"This is the Knower of the unseen and the seen, the Mighty the Merciful"
  32,7,"Who made good everything that He has created, and He began the creation of man from dust"
  32,8,"Then He made his progeny of an extract, of a fluid held in low esteem"
  32,9,"Then He fashioned him and breathed into him of His spirit, and made for you the faculties of hearing, and sight and heart; little is it that you give thanks"
  32,10,"And they say: What! When we have become lost in the earth, shall we then certainly be a new creation? Nay! They are disbelievers in the meeting with their Lord"